Crash in FT_Set_Transform, signature crash -BBBF
e.g. http://crash/reportdetail?reportid=7674dafd2048c734

64-bit only, so no stacks.  :(

From the addresses it looks like FT_Set_Transform:
0x000000000000bbb0 &lt;FT_Set_Transform+0&gt;:	test   %rdi,%rdi
0x000000000000bbb3 &lt;FT_Set_Transform+3&gt;:	je     0xbc16 
&lt;FT_Set_Transform+102&gt;
0x000000000000bbb5 &lt;FT_Set_Transform+5&gt;:	mov    0xf0(%rdi),%rcx
0x000000000000bbbc &lt;FT_Set_Transform+12&gt;:	test   %rsi,%rsi
0x000000000000bbbf &lt;FT_Set_Transform+15&gt;:	movl   $0x0,0x38(%rcx)

which means rcx is NULL.


FT_EXPORT_DEF( void )
  FT_Set_Transform( FT_Face     face,
                    FT_Matrix*  matrix,
                    FT_Vector*  delta )
  {
    FT_Face_Internal  internal;


    if ( !face )
      return;

    internal = face-&gt;internal;

    internal-&gt;transform_flags = 0;

So internal is NULL.

No idea why this can happen.

